==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Slow
<hw>Slow</hw> <pr>(sl⟦omac⟧)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos> <adjf>Slower</adjf>
<pr>(sl⟦omac⟧"⟦etil⟧r)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Slowest</adjf>.]</amorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>slow</ets>,
<ets>slaw</ets>, AS. <ets>sl⟦amac⟧w</ets>; akin to OS.
<ets>sl⟦emac⟧u</ets> blunt, dull, D. <ets>sleeuw</ets>, <ets>slee</ets>,
sour, OHG. <ets>sl⟦emac⟧o</ets> blunt, dull, Icel. <ets>sl⟦omac⟧r</ets>,
<ets>sl⟦ae⟧r</ets>, Dan. <ets>sl⟦oum⟧v</ets>, Sw. <ets>sl⟦oum⟧</ets>.
Cf. <er>Sloe</er>, and <er>Sloth</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Moving a
short space in a relatively long time; not swift; not quick in motion;
not rapid; moderate; deliberate; <as>as, a <ex>slow</ex> stream; a
<ex>slow</ex> motion</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not happening in a short time; gradual;
late.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>These changes in the heavens, though <qex>slow</qex>, produced⟦br⟧
Like change on sea and land, sidereal blast.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Not ready; not prompt or quick; dilatory; sluggish;
<as>as, <ex>slow</ex> of speech, and <ex>slow</ex> of
tongue</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Fixed on defense, the Trojans are not <qex>slow</qex>⟦br⟧
To guard their shore from an expected foe.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Not hasty; not precipitate; acting with
deliberation; tardy; inactive.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He that is <qex>slow</qex> to wrath is of great understanding.</q>
<rj><qau>Prov. xiv. 29.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>Behind in time; indicating a time earlier than the
true time; <as>as, the clock or watch is <ex>slow</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>6.</sn> <def>Not advancing or improving rapidly; <as>as, the
<ex>slow</ex> growth of arts and sciences</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>7.</sn> <def>Heavy in wit; not alert, prompt, or spirited;
wearisome; dull.</def> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark> <rj><au>Dickens.
Thackeray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ <xex>Slow</xex> is often used in the formation of
compounds for the most part self-explaining; as, <xex>slow</xex>-gaited,
<xex>slow</xex>-paced, <xex>slow</xex>-sighted, <xex>slow</xex>-winged,
and the like.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Slow coach</b></col>, <cd>a slow person. See def.7,
above.</cd> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark> -- <mcol><col><b>Slow
lemur</b></col>, <it>or</it> <col><b>Slow loris</b></col></mcol>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd> an East Indian nocturnal lemurine animal
(<spn>Nycticebus tardigradus</spn>) about the size of a small cat; -- so
called from its slow and deliberate movements. It has very large round
eyes and is without a tail. Called also <altname>bashful
Billy</altname>.</cd> -- <col><b>Slow match</b></col>. <cd>See under
<er>Match</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Dilatory; late; lingering; tardy; sluggish; dull;
inactive.</syn> -- <usage><er>Slow</er>, <er>Tardy</er>,
<er>Dilatory</er>. <xex>Slow</xex> is the wider term, denoting either a
want of rapid motion or inertness of intellect. <xex>Dilatory</xex>
signifies a proneness to <xex>defer</xex>, a habit of delaying the
performance of what we know must be done. <xex>Tardy</xex> denotes the
habit of being behind hand; as, <xex>tardy</xex> in making up one's
acounts.</usage>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Slow</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Slow
<hw>Slow</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>Slowly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Let him have time to mark how <qex>slow</qex> time goes⟦br⟧
In time of sorrow.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Slow</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Slow
<hw>Slow</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Slowed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Slowing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To render slow; to slacken the
speed of; to retard; to delay; <as>as, to <ex>slow</ex> a
steamer</as>.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Slow</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 5 ====
HEADWORD: Slow
<hw>Slow</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To go slower; -- often with
<xex>up</xex>; <as>as, the train <ex>slowed</ex> up before crossing the
bridge</as>.</def> <-- also with down. -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Slow</ent>⟦br⟧

